<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xml:lang="en"><generator uri="https://gohugo.io/" version="0.82.0">Hugo</generator><title type="html">peek on Sebastian Hoß</title><link href="https://seb.people.metio.wtf/tags/peek/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="HTML"/><link href="https://seb.people.metio.wtf/tags/peek/index.xml" rel="alternate" type="application/rss+xml" title="RSS"/><link href="https://seb.people.metio.wtf/tags/peek/atom.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" title="Atom"/><updated>2021-04-19T02:41:01+00:00</updated><id>https://seb.people.metio.wtf/tags/peek/</id><entry><title type="html">Peeking with tmux</title><link href="https://seb.people.metio.wtf/topic/peeking-with-tmux/?utm_source=atom_feed" rel="alternate" type="text/html"/><id>https://seb.people.metio.wtf/topic/peeking-with-tmux/</id><published>2021-04-05T00:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2021-04-05T00:00:00+00:00</updated><content type="html"><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://github.com/tmux/tmux">tmux</a> uses can use the following snippet to peek at files. Place it in your <code>.bashrc</code> or similar file.</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre class="chroma"><code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell">peek<span class="o">()</span> <span class="o">{</span> tmux split-window -p <span class="m">33</span> <span class="s2">&#34;</span><span class="nv">$EDITOR</span><span class="s2">&#34;</span> <span class="s2">&#34;</span><span class="nv">$@</span><span class="s2">&#34;</span> <span class="o">}</span>
</code></pre></div><p>Calling <code>peek &lt;file&gt;</code> will open <code>&lt;file&gt;</code> in lower third of tmux window.</p>
]]></content><category scheme="https://seb.people.metio.wtf/categories/snippet" term="snippet" label="snippet"/><category scheme="https://seb.people.metio.wtf/tags/tmux" term="tmux" label="tmux"/><category scheme="https://seb.people.metio.wtf/tags/peek" term="peek" label="peek"/></entry></feed>